def get_california_dataset():
    """Return the splits of the California housing dataset for training and testing"""
    X, y = fetch_california_housing(return_X_y=True)
    return train_test_split(X, y, random_state=42)

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = get_california_dataset()

# your code here
tree_no_scaling = DecisionTreeRegressor(max_depth=10, random_state=0)
tree_no_scaling.fit(X_train, y_train)
tree1_preds = tree_no_scaling.predict(X_test)

tree_pipe = Pipeline([
    ('scaler', MinMaxScaler()),
    ('tree', DecisionTreeRegressor(max_depth=10, random_state=0))
])
tree_pipe.fit(X_train, y_train)
tree2_preds = tree_pipe.predict(X_test)

ridge_no_scaling = RidgeCV(alphas= [0.1, 1.0, 10], store_cv_values=True)
ridge_no_scaling.fit(X_train, y_train)
ridge_no_scaling_preds = ridge_no_scaling.predict(X_test)

ridge_pipeline = Pipeline([
    ('scaler', MinMaxScaler()),
    ('ridge', RidgeCV(alphas= [0.1, 1.0, 10], store_cv_values=True))
])
ridge_pipeline.fit(X_train, y_train)
ridge_scaled_preds = ridge_pipeline.predict(X_test)

tree_mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, tree1_preds)
tree_scaled_mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, tree2_preds)
ridge_mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, ridge_no_scaling_preds)
ridge_scaled_mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, ridge_scaled_preds)

print(f"  ( ) MAE: {tree_mae:.4f}")
print(f"  ( ) MAE: {tree_scaled_mae:.4f}")
print(f"Ridge ( ) MAE: {ridge_mae:.4f}")
print(f"Ridge ( ) MAE: {ridge_scaled_mae:.4f}")
